# Shell scripts ship to / run on the Linux appliance — keep them LF so a
# Windows checkout can't introduce CRLF that would break the shebang
# (`/bin/sh^M: bad interpreter`). Covers the dev-installer template whose
# output is published as a release asset, and all on-device helper scripts.
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.sh.tmpl   text eol=lf
*.hook.chroot text eol=lf
